{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place prunes into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 150 g of the water and bicarbonate of soda and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into bowl with the chocolate and set aside.","Place butter and sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs, self-raising flour, cinnamon, cardamom, cloves and reserved chocolate-prune mixture and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat mixing <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Transfer batter into 18 silicone cupcake moulds and fill so they are ¾ full. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place remaining 1000 g of the water into mixing bowl, then place Varoma into position.","Arrange 9 of the filled silicone moulds into Varoma dish and onto Varoma tray. Set remaining 9 silicone moulds aside.","Place a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper, then a piece of paper towel, on top of the puddings in Varoma dish and tray. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>18-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until puddings are cooked. Remove Varoma and place puddings into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Place Varoma back into position and repeat with remaining 9 silicone moulds, covering again with a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper, followed by a piece of paper towel. Secure Varoma lid, then repeat steaming <b>18-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until puddings are cooked.","Serve puddings warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g dark chocolate, broken into pieces","250 g pitted prunes","1150 g water","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","125 g butter, softened","200 g brown sugar","3 eggs","200 g self-raising flour","½ tsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp ground cardamom","¼ tsp ground cloves"]}],"id":"r89727","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-dU3A1uVv08A\/XZaoka7k3JI\/AAAAAAAAhLU\/F_4T5dnRJiQBKbqQiwNcsJGXQRFkMpLhgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rzcFWKk1KkNgaIkm.png","title":"Steamed chocolate and prune puddings","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"7.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27 g","calories":"779 kJ \/ 185 kcal"},"usefulItems":"18 silicone cupcake moulds, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, baking paper, paper towel, oven","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Baked chocolate and prune pudding:<\/strong> In step 6, transfer batter into a round baking dish (1300 mL capacity). Bake in the oven for 30 minutes at 160°C, then cover with aluminium foil and bake for a further 30-45 minutes (160°C) or until a wooden skewer comes out clean.","Serve warm puddings with <em>Brandy cream<\/em> or <em>Brandy butter<\/em>. For a decadent chocolate dessert make a Chocolate ganache to drizzle over the top (see <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>).","Puddings can be made up to 1-2 weeks prior to Christmas, then frozen. Remove puddings from freezer 1 hour before serving. Place 500 g water into mixing bowl and steam <strong>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong> to heat puddings to serve."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","18 portions"]}